<dl id="n09072c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09072c">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09072c"> 72(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> (peau de) Chagrin <font face="wake">C</font> <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n09072c"> <li>FW unlocated</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Comment d&apos;ailleurs concevoir cette pr&eacute;tendue action de l&apos;imagination de la m&egrave;re? Geoffroy-Saint-Hilaire a tr&egrave;s bien d&eacute;montr&eacute;, d&apos;apr&egrave;s la proportion des enfants naturels aux enfants l&eacute;gitimes, que la contention d&apos;esprit, le chagrin et les maladies qui en peuvent r&eacute;sulter ne doivent pas &ecirc;tre consid&eacute;r&eacute;s comme pr&eacute;disposant une m&egrave;re &agrave; mettre un enfant diffone au jour &hellip;. <br><font color="green">[Moreover, how can we understand this supposed action of the mother&apos;s imagination? From the proportion of natural children to legitimate children, Geoffroy-Saint-Hilaire has very clearly demonstrated that the discord of the mind, grief, and illness that can result should not be considered as predisposing a mother to give birth to a deformed child]</font> <small> Caufeynon, <a name="CAUF" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CAUF"><cite title="source">Les Monstres Humains</cite></a> (Paris, 1900) ?27f</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: See also <a name="n17036c" href="n17all.htm#n17036c">N17 (VI.B.9):036(c)</a> and <a name="n17036d" href="n17all.htm#n17036d">N17 (VI.B.9):036(d)</a> for <cite>FW</cite> 186.08. </mm> </dd></dl>
